Rating: 3
This is a quick-fix meal that I have made 10+ times since finding the recipe, definitely a go-to recipe for me. Some reviewers have made some strange substitutions, which would change the flavor profile and texture completely; I recommend sticking with the original recipe and just adding one or two Mediterranean ingredients, such as chopped sun-dried tomatoes, kalamata olives or roasted red peppers, which enhance both flavor and color. I really enjoy the top crunchy pasta layer that creates a wonderful texture similar to pegao or tah-dig, so I tend to bake it in a shallow dish to increase the surface area. Its definitely not the most gourmet recipe, but if youre in a hurry and have quality ingredients on hand, its great.

