This was delicious, creamy, comforting dish. This is one of those recipes that can be changed in a million different ways depending on what you have on hand or what's on sale at the market. I substituted brocolini for the rabe and used hot sausage. It made for a wonderful, light (light-tasting, not low-fat) Sunday dinner to watch the closing ceremonies of the Olympics.

Rating: 1
I was very disappointed in this recipe. The picture looks a lot better than it tastes. I made a few changes of my own, I used chicken instead of sausage and frozen broccoli for the broccoli rabe, I used linguine instead of spaghetti and shredded monterey jack instead of cubed. I also cooked it in a a pie plate and it took a lot longer than 25 minutes. Did anyone else find that that 8 eggs was way too much. The pie was very heavy and I don't mean on your stomach kind, I'm talking about heavy like a brick. I can tell you I will not be making this again, but if I did here's what I'd do differently with the egg mixture, use only 4-5 eggs and I cup of milk, half & half or heavy cream, like a quiche. the custard will be a lot lighter and fluffier and that is what I should have done in the first place.

