Rating: 2
Previous reviewers had it right, bland and boring. I added more of everything, including some salt, pepper, oregano, and red pepper flake, and it still ended up tasting of very little except pasta and egg. Perhaps hot sausage would help, and then saute the broccoli briefly in the drippings, add onion and lots of garlic, then pour the whole mess into a bowl with pasta and eggs, then season liberally again. Also, I tried to make mine in the morning and the egg mixture sank to the bottom, so although all the components can be made ahead, don't try putting it together before you are ready to cook.

