Rating: 3
Yummy, quick and easy! After reading the reviews I made the following changes: I doubled the sliced garlic and sauteed it along with a chopped onion in olive oil. Then added the sausage to the pan. I then added the broccoli rabe directly into the pan without precooking. I had Fontinella handy and also sprayed a glass deep dish pie plate with Pam and baked 30 minutes (I had jumbo eggs available and they called for more cooking time). The spice of the hot sausage and flavors of the broccoli rabe and Fontinella were all well blended. My Italian mother loved this dish. I might try to use individual serving sized pans next time for an interesting presentation.

